# pnpm / node commands in this project

This project uses **pnpm** as its package manager.

When running **pnpm** or **node** (e.g. `pnpm install`, `pnpm dev`, `pnpm dlx`) in the terminal, prepend PATH so Homebrew's Node is used and Volta is bypassed. Otherwise the sandbox may hit "Volta error: Node is not available".

Use:

```bash
PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH" pnpm install
```

or for any pnpm/node command:

```bash
PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH" <command>
```

Examples:
- `PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH" pnpm install`
- `PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH" pnpm dev`
- `PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH" pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button`
